commit.message:
Use special type to mark end of line in OutputStream

Relying on the address of std::endl is a std library specific behaviour. For
example in libc++ it's inline function so it may have many addresses depending
on the translation unit.

This leads to different behaviour of osg::Node serialization using
osgDB::ReaderWriter for osgt format.

fixes clang and gcc misleading indentation warnings

replace tabs with spaces; another cause of misleading indentation

change back

change back

change back

Cull empty nodes (i.e. nodes with invalid bounds)

These are fairly common when doing skeleton animation - nodes that are used for the mesh skinning only, but don't have mesh children themselves. Results in nice speed up in OpenMW (~10% faster culling)

Fix outdated comment in LightSource.

Fix intersectors.

Fix invisible stats graph due to the node being culled

The node has no vertices set by default and only sets them in the draw callback which happens post culling - causing issues with the optimization in commit e28bd0e6ee3346e4025cab8c7631090b0ba559c3

Fix bug in osgFX::Effect introduced by 94dc5b10ef81fff2077

osgParticle: dynamically allocate _particles

Makes the std::sort much faster (only need to exchange pointers, not complete Particle objects).

The render_vertex_array has been temporarily removed because it relied on the particles stored contiguously in memory.
